s_2e3ba011%2Fukraine_10fdf69d.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOECD%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20Ukraine's%20economy%20has%20proved%20resilient%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifw-kiel.de%2Ftopics%2Fwar-against-ukraine%2Fukraine-support-tracker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24220%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Western%20military%20aid%20and%20to%20its%20private%20and%20state-run%20companies%20shifting%20their%20focus%20toward%20the%20country's%20defense%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20a%20different%20economy%20is%20emerging%20in%20front%20of%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Kuleba%20told%20BI%2C%20one%20where%20he%20said%20the%20private%20sector%20could%20also%20%26quot%3Bmassively%26quot%3B%20leverage%20Ukraine's%20defense%20technologies%2C%20such%20as%20AI-piloted%20drones%20and%20autonomous%20vehicles%20used%20on%20the%20front%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20cannot%20the%20same%20technology%20be%20applied%20to%20analyzing%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20movement%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20optimizing%20them%20to%20make%20them%20more%20cost-efficient%20and%20customer-oriented%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226f1b3dd4-f381-4d14-bb2d-f2e48923bb16%5C%22%3EArsenal%20of%20the%20Free%20World%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKuleba%20is%20not%20the%20only%20former%20official%20who%20sees%20huge%20potential%20in%20Ukraine's%20defense%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20Kamyshin%2C%20Ukraine's%20former%20minister%20of%20strategic%20industries%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fnov%2F26%2Fukraine-arms-boss-oleksandr-kamyshin-arsenal-of-the-free-world%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November%202023%20that%20Ukraine%20could%20become%20the%20%26quot%3Barsenal%20of%20the%20free%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20economic%20and%20military%20analysts%20have%20also%20predicted%20that%20Ukraine%20will%20become%20a%20European%20defense%20powerhouse%20after%20the%20war%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Courtney%2C%20an%20adjunct%20senior%20fellow%20at%20RAND%20Corporation%20and%20a%20former%20US%20ambassador%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Ukraine%20could%20become%20a%20cost-competitive%20producer%20of%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20military%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20be%20useful%20given%20that%20many%20European%20countries%20lack%20the%20capability%20to%20produce%20some%20items%20or%20the%20capacity%20to%20produce%20them%20in%20sufficient%20volume%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECourtney%20pointed%20to%20software%2C%20AI%2C%20robotics%2C%20and%20wheeled%20vehicles%20as%20key%20areas%20Ukraine%20has%20developed%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%2C%20and%20where%20it%20could%20lead%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20a%20decade%20after%20combat%20operations%20end%20and%20a%20stable%20cease-fire%20or%20armistice%20is%20achieved%2C%20Ukraine%20could%20become%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20top%2010%20countries%20in%20terms%20of%20defense%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Krukovets%2C%20a%20macroeconomic%20analyst%20at%20the%20Kyiv%20School%20of%20Economics%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20expects%20Ukraine%20to%20be%20a%20strong%20player%20after%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Brapid%20rise%26quot%3B%20in%20military-tech%20startups%20and%20defense%20innovations%2C%20citing%20an%20October%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkse.ua%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2F241004-Brave1-report-v.1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Brave1%20and%20the%20Kyiv%20School%20of%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20study%20found%20that%20Ukrainian%20defense%20startups%20raised%20%245%20million%20in%202023%2C%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elooked%20set%20to%20raise%20%2450%20million%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20da