ade%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-quantitative-easing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equantitative%20easing%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20near-zero%20interest%20rates%20and%20eventually%20wider%20support%20for%20modern%20monetary%20theory%2C%20which%20champions%20government%20spending%20to%20stabilize%20the%20economy.%20It%20also%20gave%20Carlile%20a%20sense%20of%20what%20future%20responses%20to%20economic%20risk%20may%20look%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20the%20stock%20market%20took%20another%20nosedive%20in%20March%202020%20as%20pandemic-driven%20fears%20led%20to%20a%20selling%20frenzy%2C%20he%20sensed%20that%20Washington%20would%20step%20in%20to%20save%20markets.%20Carlile%20is%20responsible%20for%20managing%20more%20than%20%242%20million%20in%20personal%20and%20family%20assets%2C%20according%20to%20financial%20statements%20viewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20panic%2C%20he%20bought%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Frisk-vs-volatility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisk-on%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%2C%20including%20call%20options%20on%20the%20Dow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%20through%20the%20SPDR%20Dow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%20ETF%20Trust%20(DIA)%20with%20June%20and%20September%20expirations%20that%20would%20rise%20in%20value%20if%20the%20index%20recovered.%20As%20the%20central%20bank%20stepped%20in%20to%20cut%20rates%2C%20provide%20forward%20guidance%2C%20and%20enact%20quantitative%20easing%2C%20the%20market%20regained%20its%20losses%20by%20June.%20Records%20from%20his%20brokerage%20statement%20showed%20Carlile%20sold%20his%20positions%20in%20positive%20territory%20in%20April%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20shutdown%20also%20led%20to%20expectations%20that%20oil%20demand%20would%20fall%20sharply%20as%20transportation%20needs%20declined.%20Using%20the%20same%20thesis%2C%20he%20went%20short%20by%20buying%20put%20options%20on%20crude%20oil%20on%20April%2016%20with%20June%2020%20expiries.%20He%20sold%20into%20the%20plunge%20a%20few%20days%20later%20before%20going%20long%20crude%20oil%20futures%20when%20West%20Texas%20Intermediate%20(WTI)%20crude%20began%20recovering.%20He%20purchased%20contracts%20with%20a%20June%20expiry%20anticipating%20that%20government%20intervention%20would%20reverse%20the%20trend.%20Oil%20prices%20partially%20recovered%20by%20early%20June.%20Records%20from%20his%20brokerage%20statements%20showed%20Carlile%20sold%20his%20positions%20in%20positive%20territory%20in%20April%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Carlile%20used%20his%20macro-driven%20strategy%20to%20snag%20first%20place%20in%20the%20World%20Cup%20Championship%20of%20Futures%20Trading%2C%20garnering%20a%20532%25%20return%2C%20according%20to%20competition%20records%20submitted%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20His%20biggest%20win%20in%202024%20came%20from%20markets%20mispricing%20Fed%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20there%20were%20high%20expectations%20for%20steep%20cuts%20that%20were%20eventually%20dashed%20by%20late%20spring%20as%20inflation%20data%20remained%20sticky%20and%20Fed%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20maintained%20a%20hawkish%20tone.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Federal%2520Open%2520Market%2520Committee%2Cbased%2520on%2520prevailing%2520economic%2520conditions.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efed%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20futures%20market%2C%20where%20traders%20bet%20on%20or%20hedge%20changes%20in%20the%20Fed's%20key%20rate%2C%20scaled%20back%20on%20the%20number%20of%20rate%20cuts%20it%20expected%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Carlile%20believed%20the%20tight%20financial%20conditions%20would%20lead%20to%20weaker%20economic%20data%20by%20summer%20and%20cause%20the%20fed%20funds%20futu