e%20chief%20production%20pilot%20for%20the%20F-35.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETest%20pilots%20are%20the%20first%20people%20to%20actually%20fly%20the%20F-35%20off%20the%20factory%20floor.%20The%20fighter%20will%20get%20airborne%20several%20times%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20two%20or%20three%20flights%20are%20with%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20before%20the%20US%20government%20goes%20through%20all%20its%20checks%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20jet%20is%20all%20good%20and%20ready%20to%20be%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Siren%2C%20the%20biggest%20difference%20when%20she%20made%20the%20transition%20from%20the%20F-16%20to%20the%20new%20F-35%20was%20the%20sheer%20amount%20of%20information%20being%20presented%20to%20the%20pilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20F-35%20is%20seen%20in%20San%20Diego%2C%20California.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67af62426630eb10385caa5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20F-35%20is%20seen%20in%20San%20Diego%2C%20California.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Carter%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESiren%20said%20that%20in%20the%20F-16%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20had%20some%20of%20that%20information%2C%20but%20it%20was%20all%20shown%20on%20multiple%20different%20displays%20or%20formats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20the%20pilot%20had%20to%20calculate%20how%20to%20use%20certain%20tactics%20or%20interpret%20the%20presented%20battlespace%20in%20their%20heads%2C%20but%20the%20F-35%20does%20all%20of%20that%20for%20the%20pilot%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20focus%20their%20efforts%20more%20on%20the%20bigger%20mission%20picture.%20Another%20F-35%20test%20pilot%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20get%20good%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftest-pilot-f-35-demands-more-than-great-flying-skills-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanaging%20all%20the%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20comparing%20the%20jet%20to%20a%20sophisticated%20video%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiren%20said%20the%20biggest%20surprise%20of%20the%20F-35%20was%20its%20flight%20controls%20in%20low-speed%20scenarios.%20The%20fifth-generation%20fighter%20jet%20is%20equipped%20with%20a%20better%20sensor%20suite%2C%20situational%20awareness%2C%20and%20data%20fusion%20capabilities%20than%20the%20F-16.%20Those%20advanced%20capabilities%20allow%20it%20to%20perform%20as%20more%20than%20a%20fighter%20jet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20advantage%20of%20the%20F-16%20has%20always%20been%20in%20its%20speed%20and%20turn%20rate%2C%20she%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20all%20the%20flight%20controls%20and%20the%20computer%20that%20runs%20the%20flight%20controls%20on%20the%20F-35%20allows%20me%20to%20intercept%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20same%20mission%20%E2%80%94%20a%20slow%2C%20low%20Cessna%20going%2080%20knots%20to%20a%20high%2C%20fast%20flyer%20going%20Mach%201.2%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20over%20900%20mph.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20helpful%20ability%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20high%20angle%20of%20attack%20that%20the%20F-35%20can%20perform%20was%20what%20caught%20me%20off%20guard%20coming%20from%20the%20F-16%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftest-pilot-shares-experience-flying-f-16-and-f-35-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739613782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67af627a6630eb10385caa65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftest-pilot-shares-experience-flying-f-16-and-f-35-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Monessa%20Balzhiser%2C%20whose%20call%20sign%20is%20%26quot%3BSiren%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20to%20Business%20Insider%20the%20surprises%20of%20moving%20from%20one%20aircraft%20to%20the%20other.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jepstein%